er%20husband.%20She's%20also%20climbed%20all%20248%20peaks%20on%20the%20Sierra%20Peaks%20Section%20Mountaineering%20Society's%20list.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20World%20Health%20Organization%2C%20the%20number%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flongevity-tips-life-advice-octogenarian-friends-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoctogenarians%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20world%20is%20expected%20to%20triple%20between%202020%20and%202050.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20getting%20old%20doesn't%20mean%20doing%20less%20or%20being%20less%20healthy%2C%20as%20Wholey%20shows.%20The%20way%20someone%20ages%20is%20mostly%20down%20to%20genes%20and%20environment%2C%20but%20it%20can%20also%20be%20impacted%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-scientifically-reduce-body-age-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elifestyle%20factors%3C%2Fa%3E%20like%20a%20healthy%20diet%2C%20exercising%2C%20and%20taking%20care%20of%20mental%20health%2C%20according%20to%20the%20National%20Institute%20on%20Aging.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWholey%20acknowledged%20that%20she%20is%20unusual%20in%20being%20so%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjoseph-maroon-aging-expert-longevity-tips-secrets-healthy-lifespan-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eactive%20for%20her%20age%3C%2Fa%3E.%20She%20said%20being%20active%20is%20%26quot%3Bautomatic%26quot%3B%20for%20her%20%E2%80%94%20she%20doesn't%20have%20a%20problem%20motivating%20herself%20to%20get%20out%20there%20and%20exercise%20because%20she%20finds%20it%20fun.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20feel%20sorry%20for%20people%20who%20cannot%20have%20these%20experiences%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BFor%20those%20people%20who%20have%20never%20seen%20a%20snowy%20mountain%2C%20for%20example.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20one%20of%20these%20people%2C%20but%20would%20like%20to%20be%20as%20active%20as%20Wholey%20is%20at%2082%2C%20she%20shared%20three%20tips%20with%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fbbfa936-fdcc-43c5-98d3-40a186eedfe6%5C%22%3EExercise%20seasonally%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20Wholey%20does%20mostly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpopular-exercise-methods-around-the-world-2018-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoutdoor%20sports%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20many%20of%20her%20activities%20are%20decided%20by%20season%20%E2%80%94%20skiing%20in%20the%20winter%2C%20and%20kayaking%20and%20paddle%20boarding%20in%20the%20summer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Wholey%20said%20that%20between%20the%20ski%20and%20kayaking%20seasons%2C%20she%20sometimes%20goes%20to%20the%20gym%20to%20do%20%26quot%3Bsquats%20and%20deadlifts%20and%20pull-ups%20and%20all%20those%20things%20that%20can%20help%20your%20body%20build%20strength.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDoing%20a%20variety%20of%20physical%20activities%20is%20great%20for%20fitness%2C%20especially%20in%20older%20age.%20The%20National%20Institute%20of%20Aging%20recommends%20people%20do%20endurance%2C%20strength%2C%20balance%2C%20and%20flexibility%20exercises%2C%20because%20each%20type%20of%20movement%20has%20different%20benefits%2C%20such%20as%20improving%20your%20endurance%20and%20preventing%20falls.%20Strength%20training%20is%20especially%20helpful%20for%20staying%20mobile%20as%20you%20age%20because%20it%20helps%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffurther-evidence-you-should-lift-weights-new-study-cancer-sarcopenia-muscle-2019-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprevent%20sarcopenia%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20you%20lose%20muscle%20mass%2C%20leading%20to%20a%20higher%20likelihood%20of%20falls.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2212fe6562-8c76-4ce6-9020-40d6448d61d5%5C%22%3EGet%20out%20of%20the%20city%20as%20much%20as%20you%20can%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20recommend%20going%20to%20the%20ocean%2C%20going%20to%20lakes%2C%20going%20to%20the%20mountains.%20Find%20someone%20with%20a%20car%2C%20and%20just%20get%20out%20of%20the%20c