igcaption%3E%3Cp%3EAnton%20Petrus%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EIt%20can%20take%20a%20decade%20to%20build%20transmission%20lines%2C%20and%20construction%20fell%20to%20an%20all-time%20low%20in%202022.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20delays%20make%20the%20US's%20aging%20power%20grid%20more%20vulnerable%20to%20extreme%20weather%20and%20blackouts.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENew%20federal%20rules%20could%20help%20break%20logjams%20over%20funding%20and%20environmental%20permits.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAmerica's%20power%20grid%20is%20old%20and%20stressed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBlackouts%20are%20on%20the%20rise%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fblackouts-power-outages-more-common-climate-change-electric-grid-infrastructure-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eas%20the%20climate%20crisis%20fuels%20more-powerful%20storms%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20as%20electricity%20demand%20booms%20from%20electric%20vehicles%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdata-centers-electricity-consumers-discounts-utilities-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edata%20centers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-georgia-became-green-manufacturing-capital-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emanufacturing%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20main%20problem%3A%20It%20takes%20way%20too%20long%20to%20build%20towering%20high-voltage%20power%20lines%20that%20carry%20electricity%20across%20state%20lines%20and%20to%20hook%20up%20new%20power%20to%20the%20grid.%20Long%20transmission%20lines%20can%20take%20more%20than%20a%20decade%20to%20build%2C%20and%20federal%20regulators%20have%20said%20their%20construction%20declined%20to%20an%20all-time%20low%20in%202022.%20Some%202.6%20terawatts%20of%20new%20power%20%E2%80%94%20more%20than%20twice%20the%20size%20of%20the%20entire%20US%20grid%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Femp.lbl.gov%2Fqueues%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eare%20backed%20up%20in%20yearslong%20connection%20queues%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20part%20because%20of%20a%20lack%20of%20capacity.%20The%20vast%20majority%20of%20that%20power%20comes%20from%20renewable-energy%20projects.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20delays%20threaten%20the%20transition%20to%20cleaner%20energy%20and%20make%20residents%20more%20vulnerable%20to%20extreme%20weather.%20States%20also%20could%20miss%20out%20on%20new%20business%20opportunities%20if%20they%20don't%20solve%20the%20power%20crunch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20help%20break%20the%20logjams%2C%20the%20federal%20government%20in%20the%20last%20month%20has%20made%20sweeping%20changes%20to%20how%20grid%20upgrades%20are%20planned%2C%20paid%20for%2C%20and%20permitted.%20Energy%20regulators%2C%20developers%2C%20and%20lawyers%20say%20that%20while%20the%20changes%20won't%20immediately%20solve%20every%20bottleneck%2C%20they%20should%20make%20the%20US%20more%20prepared%20for%20skyrocketing%20energy%20demand%20and%20extreme%20weather.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20grid%20as%20it%20exists%20now%20is%20essentially%20tapped%20out.%20There's%20no%20headroom%20left%20on%20the%20system%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Brett%20White%2C%20a%20vice%20president%20of%20regulatory%20affairs%20at%20Pine%20Gate%20Renewables%2C%20an%20energy%20developer%20with%20projects%20in%2030%20states.%20%26quot%3BBut%20if%20I%20zoom%20out%20and%20take%20a%20long%20view%2C%20I'm%20optimistic%20about%20the%20future%20reliability%20of%20the%20grid.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a9d87384-b76f-4e64-aa11-1d747749baf2%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Nobody%20wants%20to%20see%20it%2C%20and%20nobody%20wants%20to%20pay%20for%20it'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.energy.gov%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F2022-04%2FQueued%2520Up%25E2%2580%25A6But%2520in%2520Need%2520of%2520Transmission.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFederal%20data%3C%2Fa%3E%20indicates%20that%20while%202%2C000%20miles%20of%20transmission%20lines%20were%20built%20on%20average%20each%20year%20from%202012%20to%202016%2C%20that%20figure%20dropped%20to%20700%20miles%20from%202017%20to%202021.%20Last%20year%2C%20just%20251%20miles%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcms.ferc.gov%2Fmedia%2Fenergy-infrastructure-update-december-2023%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecompleted%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frepeatproject.org%2Fdocs%2FREPEAT_IRA_Transmission_2022-09-22.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egroup%20of%20researchers%20led%20by%20Princeton%20University%20found%20in%202022%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20to%20meet%20its%20goals%20for%20cleaner%20electricity%2C%20the%20US%20would%20need%20to%20more%20than%20double%20the%20previous%20decade's%20pace%20of%20transmission%20expansion.%20That's%20because%20many%20of%20the%20places%20with%20the%20most%20wind%20and%20solar%20potential%20are%20in%20parts%20of%20the%20country%20without%20the%20infrastructure%20to%20carry%20the%20electricity%20to%20homes%20and%20businesses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20upgrading%20the%20power%20grid%20gets%20bogged%20down%20by%20several%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20regional%20authorities%20that%20oversee%20the%20grid%20aren't%20doing%20much%20long-term%20planning%20to%20make%20sure%20there's%20enough%20transmission%20capacity.%20They%20tend%20to%20be%20reactionary%2C%20acting%20only%20when%2C%20for%20example%2C%20a%20solar%20developer%20wants%20to%20connect%20to%20the%20grid%20or%20a%20reliability%20issue%20pops%20up.%20Securing%20permits%20for%20transmission%20projects%20involves%20a%20patchwork%20of%20state%20and%20federal%20agencies%2C%20and%20locals%20often%20oppose%20energy%20infrastructure%20in%20their%20backyards.%20States%20with%20clashing%20priorities%20also%20fight%20over%20who%20pays%20for%20the%20costly%20power%20lines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20a%20gross%20oversimplification%2C%20but%20to%20summarize%20the%20problem%20succinctly%3A%20Nobody%20wants%20to%20see%20it%2C%20and%20nobody%20wants%20to%20pay%20for%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Larry%20Gasteiger%2C%20the%20executive%20director%20of%20Wires%2C%20a%20trade%20group%20that%20advocates%20for%20transmission%20development.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20new%20rule%20issued%20by%20the%20Federal%20Energy%20Regulatory%20Commission%20this%20month%20is%20aimed%20at%20tackling%20some%20of%20the%20problems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20commission%20directed%20regional%20grid%20operators%2C%20states%2C%20and%20utilities%20to%20develop%2020-year%20transmission%20plans%20to%20support%20rapidly%20growing%20electricity%20demand%20and%20provide%20a%20fair%20way%20to%20pay%20for%20it.%20The%20rule%20also%20makes%20it%20harder%20for%20states%20to%20opt%20out.%20The%20goal%20is%20to%20make%20the%20grid%20more%20reliable%20and%20keep%20costs%20down%20for%20customers%20in%20the%20long%20run.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAllison%20Clements%2C%20a%20Democrat%20on%20the%20commission%2C%20noted%20that%20the%20agency%20recently%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.utilitydive.com%2Fnews%2Fferc-pjm-exelon-transmission-plan-talen-brandon-shores-psc%2F699410%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eapproved%20nearly%20%241%20billion%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20%26quot%3Blast-minute%26quot%3B%20transmission%20spending%20to%20avoid%20reliability%20issues%20when%20a%20single%20coal%20plant%20in%20Maryland%20closes%20in%202025.%20She%20said%20the%20regional%20grid%20operator%20%E2%80%94%20an%20entity%20known%20as%20PJM%20Interconnection%20that%20spans%2013%20states%20from%20Pennsylvania%20to%20West%20Virginia%20%E2%80%94%20could%20have%20found%20a%20more%20cost-effective%20solution%20if%20it%20had%20planned%20for%20that%20retirement%20earlier.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJeffrey%20Shields%2C%20a%20spokesman%20for%20PJM%2C%20said%20in%20an%20email%20that%20the%20organization%20is%20studying%20the%20impact%20of%20the%20FERC%20rule.%20Before%20it%20was%20issued%2C%20PJM%20was%20working%20on%20%26quot%3Blong-term%20scenario%20planning%26quot%3B%20and%20last%20year%20authorized%20a%20record%20%246.8%20billion%20in%20transmission%20projects.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERegarding%20the%20coal%20plant%20in%20Maryland%2C%20Shields%20pointed%20to%20a%20letter%20that%20PJM's%20CEO%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pjm.com%2F-%2Fmedia%2Fabout-pjm%2Fwho-we-are%2Fpublic-disclosures%2F20231205-pjm-board-response-to-sierra-club-letter-regarding-pjm-interconnections-role-in-the-maryland-energy-transition.ashx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EManu%20Asthana's%20letter%20to%20Sierra%20Club%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20December.%20Asthana%20said%20it%20wasn't%20%26quot%3Breasonable%20to%20expect%20PJM%20to%20have%20anticipated%20the%20imminent%26quot%3B%20closure%20because%20the%20owner%20of%20the%20coal%20plant%2C%20Talen%20Energy%2C%20had%20said%20it%20would%20stay%20online%20with%20oil%20as%20a%20fuel%20source.%20It%20wasn't%20until%20April%202023%20that%20PJM%20was%20notified%20about%20the%20closure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20region%20illustrates%20why%20states%20can%20clash%20over%20who%20pays.%20Maryland%20and%20New%20Jersey%20are%20aiming%20for%20100%25%20renewable%20energy%20by%202035%2C%20but%20Pennsylvania%20and%20West%20Virginia%20are%20doubling%20down%20on%20gas%20and%20coal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStates%20and%20utilities%20reliant%20on%20fossil%20fuels%20don't%20want%20to%20pay%20for%20transmission%20projects%20that%20unlock%20cleaner%20power%20to%20compete%20with%2C%20and%20they%20worry%20their%20residents%20will%20unfairly%20get%20stuck%20with%20a%20multibillion-dollar%20tab.%20Mark%20Christie%2C%20a%20Republican%20commissioner%2C%20endorsed%20that%20view%2C%20arguing%20that%20the%20agency's%20rules%20%26quot%3Bfails%20to%20protect%20consumers%26quot%3B%20and%20would%20transfer%20wealth%20to%20%26quot%3Bfor-profit%20special%20interests%26quot%3B%20like%20wind%20and%20solar%20developers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProponents%20of%20the%20commission's%20rule%20said%20that%20view%20was%20short-sighted.%20A%20well-planned%20grid%20has%20benefits%20beyond%20ushering%20in%20more%20renewable%20energy.%20Numerous%20power-hungry%20data%20centers%20and%20factories%20are%20coming%20online%2C%20and%20the%20climate%20crisis%20is%20fueling%20more%20frequent%20and%20destructive%20storms.%20If%20the%20US%20doesn't%20invest%20in%20regional%20transmission%20lines%2C%20customers%20will%20pay%20the%20price%20in%20the%20form%20of%20congestion%20and%20more%20life-threatening%20outages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGrids%20are%20being%20pushed%20to%20the%20brink%2C%26quot%3B%20Neil%20Chatterjee%2C%20a%20former%20chairman%20of%20the%20FERC%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BClimate%20change%20doesn't%20care%20about%20state%20politics%20and%20market%20design.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChatterjee%20added%20that%20it%20could%20take%20years%20for%20the%20rule%20to%20have%20an%20effect%20and%20that%20the%20commission%20would%20likely%20face%20legal%20challenges.%20But%20he%20expects%20it%20to%20be%20upheld%20because%20it%20falls%20under%20FERC's%20traditional%20authority%20to%20keep%20the%20grid%20reliable%20in%20an%20affordable%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220c1ac372-28e0-4f03-891e-725151c00a77%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ENo%20silver%20bullet%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20that%20process%20plays%20out%2C%20the%20federal%20government%20is%20also%20trying%20to%20more%20quickly%20grant%20environmental%20permits%20for%20transmission%20lines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Department%20of%20Energy%20this%20month%20said%20it%20would%20take%20the%20lead%20on%20applications%20and%20aim%20to%20issue%20decisions%20within%20two%20years%20%E2%80%94%20about%20twice%20as%20fast%20as%20its%20current%20average.%20By%20DOE%20being%20the%20main%20point%20of%20contact%2C%20project%20developers%20won't%20have%20to%20navigate%20different%20processes%20with%20eight%20different%20federal%20agencies%20in%20some%20cases.%20The%20department%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.energy.gov%2Fgdo%2Fnational-interest-electric-transmission-corridor-designation-process%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ealso%20identified%2010%20regions%20of%20the%20country%3C%2Fa%3E%20where%20some%203%2C500%20miles%20of%20transmission%20lines%20should%20be%20prioritized%20because%20customers%20are%20facing%20higher%20utility%20bills%20and%20power%20disruptions%20from%20extreme%20weather.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20that%20list%20is%20finalized%2C%20FERC%20would%20also%20be%20able%20to%20step%20in%20and%20approve%20permits%20for%20projects%20stalled%20or%20denied%20at%20the%20state%20level%20in%20those%20priority%20regions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChristine%20Powell%2C%20a%20deputy%20managing%20attorney%20of%20Earthjustice's%20Clean%20Energy%20Program%2C%20said%20that%20collectively%20these%20actions%20would%20help%20expand%20transmission%20on%20a%20%26quot%3Bpretty%20large%20scale.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20federal%20regulators%20still%20have%20few%20tools%20to%20resolve%20local%20environmental%20and%20property-rights%20disputes%20in%20vast%20swaths%20of%20the%20country%20%E2%80%94%20another%20major%20obstacle%20to%20the%20switch%20to%20cleaner%20energy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%202023%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fepic.uchicago.edu%2Fnews%2Fnew-poll-2-in-5-would-consider-purchasing-an-electric-vehicle-as-their-next-car-but-they-remain-prohibitively-expensive-for-americans%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esurvey%20by%20the%20University%20of%20Chicago%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%2056%25%20of%20Americans%20said%20they%20supported%20building%20transmission%20lines%20to%20carry%20renewable%20power%20where%20it's%20needed%2C%20but%20that%20dropped%20to%2048%25%20when%20they%20were%20told%20the%20project%20would%20be%20built%20in%20their%20neighborhood.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECongress%20and%20federal%20regulators%20also%20haven't%20addressed%20transmission%20projects%20designed%20to%20connect%20the%20country's%20fragmented%20regional%20grids%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20carrying%20Wyoming's%20wind%20power%20into%20California%2C%20where%20rolling%20blackouts%20are%20on%20the%20rise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECongress%20