0then%20submit%20it%20to%20the%20insurance%20company%2C%20which%20would%20then%20balk%20at%20reimbursing%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20thought%20it%20would%20save%20us%20money%20in%20the%20long%20run%20if%20we%20got%20it%2C%20but%20then%20they%20would%20refute%20claims%20and%20say%2C%20'Well%2C%20this%20could%20have%20been%20a%20preexisting%20condition%2C'%20and%20preexisting%20conditions%20aren't%20covered%2C%26quot%3B%20Papini%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20need%20extra%20vet%20paperwork%20to%20back%20up%20that%20it%20wasn't.%20And%20so%20then%20you%20just%20get%20to%20a%20point%20where%20you're%20jumping%20through%20so%20many%20hoops.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPapini%20and%20her%20husband%20got%20tired%20of%20dealing%20with%20all%20the%20rigamarole%20and%20axed%20their%20insurance%20plan%20after%20a%20year.%20Despite%20paying%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20in%20premiums%2C%20they%20never%20saw%20a%20single%20reimbursement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhalf-owners-say-pets-equal-human-family-member-survey-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPeople%20love%20their%20pets%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20they're%20willing%20to%20do%20a%20lot%20for%20them%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprotect-finances-pets-likely-recession-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efinancially%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20otherwise.%20The%20American%20Pet%20Products%20Association%20has%20estimated%20that%20Americans%20spent%20%24147%20billion%20on%20their%20animals%20in%202023%2C%20including%20%2438%20billion%20on%20their%20healthcare.%20This%20level%20of%20attachment%20has%20helped%20turn%20the%20pet-insurance%20industry%20into%20a%20lucrative%20and%20rapidly%20expanding%20market.%20The%20North%20American%20Pet%20Health%20Insurance%20Association%20found%20that%20pet%20owners%20in%20the%20US%20paid%20%243.9%20billion%20in%20premiums%20in%202023%2C%20a%2022%25%20increase%20from%20the%20year%20before.%20Some%206.25%20million%20pets%20in%20the%20US%20were%20insured%20as%20of%20the%20end%20of%202023%2C%20per%20NAPHIA.%20That's%20still%20a%20small%20fraction%20of%20all%20the%20pets%20in%20the%20country%2C%20given%20that%20there%20are%20over%2080%20million%20pet%20dogs%20and%2060%20million%20pet%20cats%2C%20according%20to%20the%20American%20Veterinary%20Medical%20Association.%20But%20it's%20growing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20pet%20insurance%20becomes%20more%20prevalent%2C%20so%20too%20do%20the%20questions%20about%20it.%20While%20some%20people%20swear%20by%20it%2C%20others%20think%20it's%20a%20scam.%20One%20thing%20is%20for%20sure%3A%20As%20the%20industry%20grows%2C%20pet%20insurance%20is%20becoming%20as%20confusing%20and%20messy%20as%20health%20insurance%20is%20for%20humans.%20It's%20barely%20regulated%2C%20and%20deciphering%20what%20it%20does%20and%20doesn't%20encompass%20can%20be%20super%20confusing.%20Just%20like%20regular%20health%20insurance%2C%20coverage%20for%20pets%20often%20winds%20up%20being%20riddled%20with%20loopholes%20and%20fine%20print%20that%20allows%20insurers%20to%20deny%20claims%2C%20declining%20to%20pay%20for%20the%20very%20care%20that%20motivated%20consumers%20to%20buy%20the%20policy%20in%20the%20first%20place.%20Because%20consumers%20pay%20up%20front%2C%20they%20often%20don't%20realize%20they%20won't%20be%20reimbursed%20until%20it's%20too%20late.%20Pet%20insurance%20gets%20pricier%20over%20time%2C%20meaning%20many%20people%20can%20no%20longer%20afford%20to%20keep%20their%20coverage%20just%20when%20they%20might%20start%20to%20need%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20short%2C%20pet%20insurance%20isn't%20a%20grift%20%E2%80%94%20some%20people%20do%20end%20up%20using%20their%20benefits.%20But%20for%20many%20people%2C%20insuring%20their%20furry%20friends%20ends%20up%20being%20a%20money%20suck.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EPet%20insurance%20isn't%20technically%20even%20health%20insurance%3B%20it%20falls%20in%20the%20property-and-casualty%20category.%20It's%20generally%20regulated%20pretty%20lightly%20by%20states.%20There%20are%20no%20broad%20federal%20regulations%20around%20it%2C%20and%20only%20a%20handful%20of%20states%20have%20laws%20and%20standards%20around%20it%20specifically.%20How%20it%20usually%20works%20is%20people%20pay%20a%20monthly%20premium%2C%20and%20after%20they've%20paid%20a%20vet%20bill%2C%20they%20submit%20it%20to%20the%20insurer%20to%20try%20to%20get%20their%20money%20back.%20Just%20as%20with%20human%20health%20insurance%2C%20there%20are%20also%20deductibles%20and%20copays%20and%20annual%20limits%20on%20how%20much%20the%20policy%20will%20pay%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20three%20categories%20of%20pet%20insurance%3A%20accident%20only%3B%20accident%20and%20illness%3B%20and%20accident%2C%20illness%2C%20and%20wellness.%20Adding%20more%20coverage%20makes%20the%20policy%20more%20expensive.%20Accident%20and%20accident-illness%20policies%20cover%20costs%20only%20if%20something%20goes%20awry%20%E2%80%94%20Rover%20gets%20into%20a%20rough%20fight%20at%20the%20dog%20park%20or%20develops%20arthritis.%20Fancier%2C%20more-comprehensive%20policies%20also%20cover%20wellness%20visits%20and%20preventive%20care%2C%20like%20dental%20care%20and%20vaccines.%20No%20matter%20the%20policy%20you%20choose%2C%20insurance%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Faverage-cost-pet-insurance%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecan%20get%20expensive%20fast%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Premiums%20generally%20go%20up%20each%20year%20as%20a%20pet%20gets%20older.%20And%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsoaring-home-car-insurance-rates-hurting-americans-finances-us-economy-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eas%20with%20many%20insurance%20products%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nbcnews.com%2Fbusiness%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fpet-insurance-dogs-cats-rising-prices-denied-claims-rcna93933%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epet-insurance%20premiums%20across%20the%20board%20are%20on%20the%20rise%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20of%20inflation%20and%20the%20increasing%20cost%20of%20care.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20big%20problem%20with%20pet%20insurance%20is%20it's%20just%20an%20expensive%20product%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Kevin%20Brasler%2C%20the%20executive%20editor%20of%20Consumers'%20Checkbook%2C%20a%20consumer%20watchdog%20group.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20going%20to%20be%20one%20of%20these%20plans%2C%20buy%20it%20when%20your%20pet's%20young%2C%20but%20just%20know%20your%20costs%20are%20likely%20going%20to%20skyrocket%20as%20time%20goes%20on.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20a%20pet%20owner%20can%20find%20an%20affordable%20policy%2C%20they%20may%20have%20trouble%20deciphering%20what's%20covered.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fpreexisting-conditions-in-dogs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPet%20insurance%20almost%20never%20covers%20preexisting%20conditions%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20what%20qualifies%20as%20preexisting%20can%20be%20quite%20broad%20and%20hard%20to%20parse.%20(It's%20wild%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fobama-jimmy-kimmel-healthcare-preexisting-conditions-2017-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewe%20used%20to%20do%20this%20for%20people%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20by%20the%20way.)%20If%20you%20get%20a%20policy%20for%20your%20puppy%20before%20it%20has%20a%20chance%20to%20develop%20any%20problems%2C%20it%20might%20be%20a%20good%20deal.%20But%20if%20you%20have%20a%2010-year-old%20dog%20with%20diabetes%2C%20that's%20a%20different%20story.%20I%20got%20some%20quotes%20from%20the%20website%20Pawlicy%20Advisor%20for%20my%20fictional%20dog%2C%20a%20mixed%20breed%20named%20Dan.%20When%20I%20changed%20the%20inputs%20to%20make%20Dan%20a%20six-month-old%20in%20optimal%20health%2C%20the%20platform%20recommended%20a%20policy%20starting%20at%20%2428%20a%20month.%20When%20Dan%20was%2010%20and%20had%20some%20issues%2C%20the%20first%20policy%20it%20suggested%20was%20%24125%2C%20and%20some%20plans%20were%20about%20%24350.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMichael%20San%20Filippo%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20the%20American%20Veterinary%20Medical%20Association%2C%20said%20in%20an%20email%20that%20the%20group%20endorsed%20the%20%26quot%3Bconcept%26quot%3B%20of%20pet%20health%20insurance%2C%20which%20can%20help%20keep%20vet%20costs%20down%20and%20save%20animals'%20lives%2C%20but%20he%20acknowledged%20that%20when%20the%20rubber%20hits%20the%20road%2C%20it%20can%20get%20hard%20to%20figure%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20important%20that%20pet%20owners%20understand%20the%20scope%20of%20what%20their%20pet%20insurance%20does%20and%20does%20not%20cover%2C%20so%20they're%20not%20caught%20off%20guard%20by%20unexpected%20payments%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20getting%20good%20advice%20on%20which%20pet-insurance%20policy%20is%20right%20for%20you%20can%20be%20a%20challenge.%20There%20are%20endless%20listicles%20recommending%20various%20policies%2C%20as%20well%20as%20websites%20dedicated%20to%20comparing%20insurers.%20The%20sheer%20volume%20of%20information%20can%20be%20hard%20to%20parse.%20It's%20also%20difficult%20to%20differentiate%20what%20is%20genuine%20advice%20and%20what's%20paid%20for.%20Many%20comparison%20tools%20get%20commissions%20for%20sales%20made%20through%20their%20platforms%2C%20so%20what%20they're%20recommending%20may%20not%20actually%20be%20the%20best%20option%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20just%20the%20one%20they'll%20make%20money%20off%20of.%20(This%20is%20true%20for%20all%20sorts%20of%20platforms%20that%20compare%20and%20recommend%20financial%20products%2C%20from%20credit%20cards%20to%20travel%20insurance.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20spread%20of%20these%20lists%20also%20points%20to%20another%20problem%20with%20the%20industry%3A%20the%20corporatization%20of%20pet%20insurance.%20Doug%20Kenney%2C%20a%20retired%20veterinarian%20who%20writes%20about%20the%20pet-insurance%20industry%2C%20said%20in%20an%20email%20that%20a%20decade%20ago%2C%20most%20pet-insurance%20companies%20were%20considered%20small%20businesses%20and%20were%20led%20by%20a%20founder%2FCEO%20with%20a%20vision%20for%20the%20company.%20Over%20time%2C%20these%20companies%20took%20on%20larger%20corporate%20structures%2C%20and%20some%20founders%20were%20pushed%20out%20by%20their%20boards.%20Nowadays%2C%20there%20are%20many%20large%20pet-insurance%20companies%2C%20some%20of%20which%20specialize%20only%20in%20pets%2C%20others%20of%20which%20are%20larger%20insurers%20that%20offer%20pet%20insurance%2C%20and%20many%20of%20which%20are%20publicly%20traded%2C%20meaning%20they%20ultimately%20answer%20to%20shareholders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20new%20structure%20has%20been%20a%20detriment%20to%20the%20industry%20with%20profit%20as%20the%20primary%20motive%20versus%20what%20is%20in%20the%20best%20interest%20of%20the%20consumer%2C%26quot%3B%20Kenney%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20used%20to%20say%20that%20pet%20insurance%20was%20a%20win%2C%20win%2C%20win%20proposition%20with%20the%20insurance%20company%2C%20veterinarians%2C%20and%20the%20policyholders%20and%20their%20pets%20all%20benefiting.%20I%20don't%20think%20that's%20the%20case%20anymore.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EReporting%20this%20story%2C%20I%20fully%20expected%20to%20come%20down%20on%20one%20side%20or%20the%20other%20on%20whether%20pet%20insurance%20is%20good%20or%20bad.%20But%20I%20really%20didn't%20come%20up%20with%20an%20answer.%20I%20heard%20about%20a%20wide%20array%20of%20experiences%20with%20pet%20insurance%2C%20from%20awesome%20to%20mediocre%20to%20awful.%20One%20woman%20saved%20%244%2C000%20on%20vet%20bills%20thanks%20to%20her%20insurance%20after%20her%20cat%20ate%20a%20pom-pom%20toy%20and%20the%20doctor%20had%20to%20fish%20it%20out.%20One%20man%20looked%20into%20getting%20coverage%20for%20his%20two%20cats%20after%20learning%20that%20both%20had%20extra%20teeth%2C%20but%20the%20minute%20they%20were%20documented%2C%20those%20overcrowded%20mouths%20became%20a%20preexisting%20condition.%20Another%20woman%20adopted%20a%20dog%20from%20Mexico%20with%20a%20%26quot%3Bpretty%20wonky%20leg%26quot%3B%20that's%20%26quot%3Bvery%20noticeable.%26quot%3B%20At%20her%20first%20vet%20appointment%20with%20the%20animal%2C%20the%20doctor%20told%20her%20to%20apply%20for%20pet%20insurance.%20She%20said%20she%20wouldn't%20note%20the%20leg%20on%20the%20dog's%20chart%20so%20the%20application%20would%20be%20approved%20%E2%80%94%20everyone%20agreeing%20to%20do%20a%20light%20amount%20of%20insurance%20fraud.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20purely%20financial%20or%20economic%20sense%2C%20pet%20insurance%20seems%20pretty%20worthless%20for%20many%20consumers.%20There%20are%20too%20many%20exceptions%2C%20too%20many%20hoops%20to%20jump%20through%2C%20and%20little%20regulatory%20recourse%20if%20you%20think%20you%20got%20taken%20for%20a%20ride.%20Unless%20something%20goes%20really%20awry%2C%20people%20pay%20more%20into%20their%20policies%20than%20they%20get%20out%20of%20them.%20Brasler%20was%20pretty%20blunt%20in%20his%20assessment%20of%20the%20overall%20product.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20really%20need%20to%20think%20carefully%20about%20'What%20kind%20of%20pet%20owner%20am%20I%3F'%20No%20judgments%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20a%20really%20expensive%20product.%20It's%20not%20likely%20to%20save%20you%20money%20down%20the%20road%2C%20and%20if%20it%20does%2C%20you're%20an%20outlier.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20value%20of%20this%20sort%20of%20insurance%20is%20emotional.%20It's%20possible%20to%20do%20some%20back-of-the-envelope%20calculations%20to%20figure%20out%20the%20lifetime%20cost%20of%20a%20policy%2C%20but%20the%20personal%20side%20of%20the%20equation%20is%20considering%20how%20much%20you're%20willing%20to%20spend%20on%20your%20furry%20friend.%20Maybe%20you%20feel%20like%20spending%20%2410%2C000%20over%20the%20course%20of%20your%20pet's%20life%20on%20insurance%20is%20worth%20it%20for%20the%20peace%20of%20mind.%20Or%20maybe%20you%20forgo%20insurance%2C%20figuring%20that%20if%20your%20companion%20has%20a%20serious%20health%20problem%2C%20you'll%20make%20the%20decision%20then%20to%20spend%20the%20money%20on%20them%20%E2%80%94%20or%20not.%20(Again%2C%20no%20judgments!)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20Papini%2C%20she's%20not%20getting%20back%20on%20the%20pet-insurance%20train.%20It%20was%20just%20too%20hard%20to%20deal%20with%2C%20and%20her%20husband%20is%20still%20cranky%20about%20the%20ordeal.%20She%20knows%20they're%20fortunate%20to%20be%20able%20to%20pay%20out%20of%20pocket%20for%20their%20animals'%20needs%2C%20which%20remain%20expensive.%20Kato%20now%20has%20cancer%2C%20and%20the%20treatments%20cost%20thousands%20of%20dollars.%20Would%20the%20insurance%20be%20worth%20it%20now%3F%20It's%20hard%20to%20know.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWho's%20to%20say%20they%20wouldn't%20have%20been%20like%2C%20'Well%2C%20he%20had%20diarrhea%20in%202017%2C%20so%20therefore%20it's%20a%20preexisting%20condition%2C'%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThen%20we%20would've%20spent%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20for%20the%20insurance%2C%20never%20been%20able%20to%20use%20it%2C%20and%20still%20had%20to%20pay%20out%20of%20pocket%20on%20top%20of%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Femily-stewart%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEmily%20Stewart%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%2C%20writing%20about%20business%20and%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fis-pet-insurance-worth-it-cost-scams-premiums-preexisting-conditions-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1716458221000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F664ccea09fc063e829b3529a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fis-pet-ins