ued%20that%20the%20aging%20of%20the%20platform%20marked%20the%20beginning%20of%20TikTok's%20decline.%20Like%20Instagram%20and%20Facebook%20before%20it%2C%20he%20suggested%20the%20once%20hot%2C%20new%20app%20was%20on%20the%20verge%20of%20descending%20into%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-is-bad-boring-fyp-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eboring%2C%20spammy%2C%20and%20oftentimes%20depressing%20%3C%2Fa%3Eplace%20to%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20just%20because%20TikTok's%20user%20base%20is%20becoming%20older%20doesn't%20mean%20that%20it's%20%26quot%3Bover%26quot%3B%20for%20the%20app.%20Instead%2C%20experts%20and%20users%20I%20spoke%20with%20suggested%20that%20the%20platform%20may%20simply%20be%20moving%20into%20a%20new%2C%20more%20mainstream%20phase%20of%20existence.%20TikTok%20may%20be%20less%20like%20Facebook%20and%20more%20like%20YouTube%2C%20which%20evolved%20from%20a%20youth-centric%20novelty%20into%20the%20most%20widely%20used%20app%20among%20Americans%20of%20all%20ages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20the%20millennial%20takeover%20doesn't%20herald%20the%20end%20of%20TikTok%2C%20it%20does%20mean%20we%20need%20to%20change%20how%20we%20think%20about%20it.%20As%20long%20as%20it%20can%20survive%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-ban-explainer-bill-courts-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS%20ban%20that%20the%20Senate%20recently%20voted%20into%20law%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20TikTok%20seems%20bound%20to%20mature%20from%20an%20app%20for%20young%20people%20into%20a%20place%20for%20everyone%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that%20means%20its%20cultural%20significance%20will%20only%20grow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ESocial-media%20platforms%20don't%20just%20die%20because%20their%20users%20get%20older.%20In%20his%20post%2C%20Broderick%20pointed%20to%20%26quot%3Benshittification%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20term%20popularized%20by%20the%20technology%20writer%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wired.com%2Fstory%