0Lorenz%2C%20a%20technology%20columnist%20for%20The%20Washington%20Post%20and%20the%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BExtremely%20Online%2C%26quot%3B%20told%20me%20she%20thought%20the%20uptick%20in%20millennial%20users%20may%20be%20good%20news%20for%20the%20platform.%20%26quot%3BMillennials%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20compared%20to%20teenagers%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20can%20be%20good%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20as%20TikTok%20moves%20to%20TikTok%20Shop%20%E2%80%94%20if%20they're%20able%20to%20capitalize%20on%20this%20shift%20and%20sell%20products%20more%20effectively%20to%20older%20users.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELorenz%20thinks%20YouTube%20is%20a%20more%20accurate%20comparison%20than%20Facebook.%20%26quot%3BYouTube%20is%20much%20more%20of%20an%20entertainment%20app%20in%20the%20way%20TikTok%20is%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20And%20lest%20we%20forget%2C%20in%20the%20years%20following%20its%202005%20launch%2C%20the%20video%20platform%20was%20also%20%26quot%3Bassociated%20with%20young%20people%20doing%20things%2C%20like%20cat%20videos%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%20Now%2C%20at%20nearly%20two%20decades%20old%2C%20YouTube%20is%20used%20by%20people%20of%20all%20ages%2C%20for%20all%20sorts%20of%20reasons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20think%20anybody%20thinks%2C%20'Oh%2C%20YouTube%2C%20it's%20so%20stodgy%20and%20lame%2C'%20like%20the%20way%20they%20do%20Facebook%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20Munger%20pointed%20out%20that%20larger%20audiences%20could%20result%20in%20more%20bland%20content%2C%20as%20creators%20try%20to%20appeal%20to%20more%20people.%20Even%20still%2C%20YouTube%20is%20by%20far%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-trusts-youtube-more-than-any-other-social-platform-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emost%20popular%20app%20among%20young%20people%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20an%20aging%20user%20base%2C%20generational%20trends%20get%20muddled.%20Just%20because%20something%20is%20going%20viral%20on%20TikTok%20doesn't%20necessarily%20mean%20Gen%20Z%20is%20behind%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20trends%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frachel-zoe-hates-gen-z-baggy-pants-trend-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elike%20baggy%20jeans%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20do%20start%20with%20Gen%20Z.%20Lewis%2C%20who%20uses%20the%20app%20primarily%20to%20study%20youth%20trends%2C%20noticed%20Gen%20Zers%20posting%20on%20TikTok%20about%20going%20to%20thrift%20stores%20to%20buy%20huge%2C%20cheap%20jeans.%20%26quot%3BThen%20millennials%20realized%20they%20couldn't%20wear%20skinny%20jeans%20anymore%2C%20so%20they're%20buying%20Citizens%20of%20Humanity%20%24200%20wide-leg%20jeans%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20definitely%20starts%20with%20the%20Gen%20Zers.%20And%20then%20the%20millennials%20get%20to%20it%2C%20and%20then%20they%20run%20with%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20trends%20happen%20in%20reverse.%20Lewis%20pointed%20to%20the%20recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennial-stanley-cup-wedding-day-harry-potter-books-quencher-collection-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EStanley-cup%20craze%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20saw%20new%20tumbler%20designs%20sell%20out%20in%20minutes%20after%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrader-joes-mini-tote-bags-stanley-cups-tiktok-consumerism-marketing-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecups%20went%20viral%20on%20TikTok%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Though%20the%20trend%20became%20synonymous%20with%20Gen%20Z%20and%20Gen%20Alpha%20kids%20trying%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstanley-cups-tearing-apart-gen-alpha-middle-schools-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eimpress%20their%20peers%20at%20school%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it%20was%20largely%20the%20product%20of%20savvy%20marketing%20by%20The%20Buy%20Guide%2C%20a%20group%20of%20three%20millennial%20shopping%20influencers%20who%20began%20singing%20the%20product's%20praises%20in%202017%20before%20partnering%20with%20Stanley%20in%202020%20to%20help%20promote%20it%20to%20new%20audiences.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn-the-know%20millennial%20moms%20caught%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20Lewis%20said.%20%26quot%3BStanley%20is%20one%20of%20the%20rare%20cases%20where%20it%20trickled%20down%20from%20millennials%20to%20Gen%20Zers%20%E2%80%94%20and%20then%2C%20of%20course%2C%20Gen%20Alpha%2C%20who%20have%20millennial%20parents%2C%20jumped%20on%20it%20as%20well.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20the%20Pew%20data%20suggested%20that%20users%20ages%2035%20to%2049%20were%20slightly%20more%20likely%20to%20upload%20videos%20than%20their%2018-%20to%2034-year-old%20peers%2C%20it's%20difficult%20to%20say%20what%20role%20older%20users%20are%20playing%20in%20sparking%20trends.%20Part%20of%20that%20comes%20down%20to%20the%20nature%20of%20TikTok%20itself.%20Munger%20pointed%20out%20that%20while%20someone%20could%20find%20that%20they're%20being%20served%20a%20lot%20of%20content%20made%20by%20older%20creators%2C%20other%20users%20could%20find%20the%20opposite%20to%20be%20true.%20Lewis%2C%20for%20her%20part%2C%20hasn't%20noticed%20a%20change.%20%26quot%3BMy%20FYP%20is%20still%20entirely%20Gen%20Zers%20doing%20funny%20things%2C%20talking%20about%20trends%2C%20talking%20about%20things%20they're%20buying%2C%26quot%3B%20Lewis%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20her%20For%20You%20page.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20people%2C%20though%2C%20have%20noticed%20a%20clear%20uptick%20in%20Y2K%20and%202000s%20nostalgia%20on%20the%20app%2C%20which%20harks%20back%20to%20a%20time%20when%20millennials%20were%20children%20or%20teenagers.%20In%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wired.com%2Fstory%2Ftiktok-milennials-2000s-aging%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epiece%20for%20Wired%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3EJason%20Parham%20pointed%20to%20a%20recent%20glut%20of%20%26quot%3BMean%20Girls%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BThe%20Sopranos%26quot%3B%20videos%20as%20evidence%20of%20the%20dawning%20reality%2C%20per%20one%20of%20his%20coworkers%2C%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20olds%20are%20in%20charge%20now.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELeslie%20Horn%20Petersen%2C%20a%20millennial%20mother%20of%20two%20and%20my%20coworker%2C%20admitted%20these%20trips%20down%20memory%20lane%20were%20part%20of%20why%20she%20loves%20using%20TikTok.%20Recently%2C%20she's%20been%20following%20a%20creator%20who%20posts%20images%20created%20using%20Kid%20Pix%2C%20a%20primitive%20drawing%20game%20that%20launched%20in%20the%20late%201980s%20as%20a%20child-friendly%20alternative%20to%20Microsoft%20Paint.%20%26quot%3BI%20remember%20having%20it%20in%20the%20computer%20labs%20at%20school%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20revival%20of%20fashion%20and%20digital%20culture%20from%20the%20turn%20of%20the%20millennium%20has%20been%20primarily%20driven%20by%20Gen%20Z%2C%20experts%20told%20me%2C%20but%20the%20growing%20millennial%20audience%20can%20help%20take%20those%20trends%20mainstream.%20As%20Munger%20sees%20it%2C%20this%20desire%20to%20participate%20in%20youth%20culture%20is%20part%20of%20what%20makes%20the%20millennial%20generation%20%E2%80%94%20and%20this%20particular%20moment%20in%20TikTok's%20evolution%20%E2%80%94%20unique.%20And%20we%20can%20probably%20chalk%20it%20up%20to%20the%20fact%20that%20many%20millennials%2C%20at%20least%20economically%20speaking%2C%20are%20still%20trapped%20in%20a%20kind%20of%20perpetual%20young%20adulthood.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20connection%20between%20the%20well-documented%20millennial%20tendency%20to%20not%20be%20able%20to%20progress%20through%20the%20life%20cycle%20for%20various%20economic%2C%20mostly%20material%2C%20reasons%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat%20has%20made%20them%20more%20interested%20in%20youth%20culture%20for%20a%20longer%20period%20of%20time%20than%20might%20have%20been%20the%20case%20for%20previous%20generations.%26quot%3B%20The%20same%20could%20be%20said%20of%20Gen%20Z%2C%20which%20would%20explain%20the%20generations'%20shared%20fascination%20with%20a%20time%20before%20smartphones%20and%20round-the-clock%20news.%20%26quot%3BIt%20just%20comes%20back%20to%2C%20we%20all%20do%20yearn%20for%20simpler%20days%2C%26quot%3B%20Lewis%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Gen%20Z%20users%20I%20spoke%20with%20didn't%20seem%20particularly%20concerned%20about%20an%20influx%20of%20olds.%20Gelfond%2C%20the%20UC%20Santa%20Barbara%20student%2C%20welcomes%20it.%20He%20uses%20TikTok%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20politics%20and%20current%20affairs%20and%20appreciates%20the%20wider%20variety%20of%20content%20that%20has%20become%20available%20as%20more%20politicians%2C%20subject-matter%20experts%2C%20and%20other%20verified%20sources%20sign%20up.%20%26quot%3BSince%20the%20development%20of%20it%20generating%20a%20larger%20millennial%20user%20base%2C%20I've%20enjoyed%20it%20more%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20can%20still%20view%20dance%20videos%20and%20social-media%20influencers%20and%20things%20like%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20you%20now%20also%20have%20the%20option%20of%20viewing%20more%20mature%20content.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESullivan%2C%20the%20comedian%2C%20sees%20the%20increased%20intergenerational%20chatter%20as%20mostly%20good-spirited.%20%26quot%3BI've%20seen%20this%20trend%20of%20older%20people%20making%20TikToks%20that%20are%20really%20funnily%20edited%20or%20dramatic%20and%20intense%2C%20and%20all%20the%20comments%20are%20Gen%20Zers%20being%20like%2C%20'Pop%20off%2C%20queen!'%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI've%20never%20seen%20any%20Gen%20Z%20be%20like%2C%20'There's%20too%20many%20older%20people%20on%20this%20app.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20TikTok%20is%20clearly%20moving%20into%20a%20new%20chapter%2C%20a%20lot%20is%20still%20up%20in%20the%20air.%20At%20the%20moment%2C%20pretty%20much%20everything%20rests%20on%20what%20happens%20with%20the%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2