l%20atmosphere%2C%20it%20has%20shown%20a%20willingness%20to%20engage%20the%20US%2C%20conscious%20of%20both%20its%20strengths%20and%20vulnerabilities.%20This%20would%20explain%20the%20series%20of%20high-level%20visits%20of%20US%20officials%20to%20China%20after%20last%20year's%20Biden-Xi%20summit%20in%20San%20Francisco.%20Beijing%20is%20confident%20that%20the%20US%20cannot%20decouple%20itself%20from%20China%20-%20the%20world's%20second-largest%20economy%2C%20the%20biggest%20manufacturing%20power%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20biggest%20exporter.%20The%20Chinese%20market%20opportunities%20are%20far%20too%20big%20to%20be%20ignored%20by%20American%20corporations.%20China%20also%20controls%20many%20critical%20technologies%20and%20raw%20materials%20that%20are%20critical%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20for%20the%20green%20transition.%20The%20US%20can%20reduce%20its%20dependence%20on%20China%20in%20a%20few%20important%20areas%2C%20but%20that%20is%20going%20to%20take%20time.%20Thus%2C%20the%20world's%20two%20biggest%20economies%20will%20have%20to%20strike%20a%20new%20balance%20of%20interests%20-%20within%20a%20security%20paradigm.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%20though%2C%20China%20is%20aware%20that%20its%20economy%20is%20facing%20headwinds.%20It%20has%20a%20vested%20interest%20in%20globalisation%20so%20as%20to%20propel%20its%20own%20growth%20and%20prosperity.%20It%20would%20like%20to%20avoid%20a%20confrontation%20with%20the%20US%20even%20as%20it%20is%20willing%20to%20push%20back%20strongly%20through%20its%20aggressive%20moves%20in%20the%20Taiwan%20Strait%20and%20the%20South%20China%20Sea%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20anti-US%20verbal%20attacks%20by%20Chinese%20leaders%20and%20spokespersons.%3Cbr%3E%5CnChina%20cannot%20ignore%20America's%20repeated%20attempts%20to%20deny%20it%20access%20to%20the%20most%20advanced%20technologies%2C%20as%20well%20as%20to%20its%20market%20by%20imposing%20prohibitive%20tariffs%20on%20products%20like%20EVs%20that%2C%20in%20America's%20view%2C%20can%20further%20damage%20its%20industrial%20base.%20The%20US%20is%20also%20developing%20its%20own%20capacities%20in%20various%20areas%2C%20such%20as%20semiconductors%2C%20to%20reduce%20its%20dependence%20on%20China%2C%20and%20aims%20to%20ultimately%20develop%20an%20industrial%20policy%20of%20its%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EGermany's%20Dependence%20On%20Europe%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina%20is%20also%20aware%20of%20the%20US's%20pressure%20on%20Europe%20to%20follow%20its%20lead%20in%20technology%20denial%20measures%20against%20it.%20Europe%20cannot%20entirely%20reject%20such%20pressures%20given%20the%20tight%20security%20linkages%20with%20the%20US.%20But%20the%20two%20have%20a%20history%20of%20sharp%20differences%20on%20many%20economic%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGermany%20is%20highly%20dependent%20on%20the%20Chinese%20market%2C%20which%20explains%20the%20recent%20Beijing%20visit%20of%20Chancellor%20Olaf%20Scholz%20accompanied%20by%20CEOs%20of%20major%20German%20corporations.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20President%20Xi%20Jinping%20visited%20France%20most%20recently%2C%20followed%20by%20a%20trip%20to%20Hungary%20and%20Serbia%2C%20both%20of%20which%20are%20demonstrably%20pro-China%20and%20at%20odds%20with%20the%20EU%20over%20the%20Ukraine%20conflict%20as%20well%20as%20the%20union's%20excessive%20liberalism.%20Already%2C%20the%20EU%20is%20concerned%20about%20China%20using%20the%20two%20nations%20to%20exploit%20the%20cracks%20in%20European%20unity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina%20would%20like%20to%20capitalise%20on%20EU-US%20differences.%20It%20has%20been%20openly%20encouraging%20Europe%20to%20play%20an%20independent%20role%20in%20international%20affairs.%20During%20his%20visit%20to%20France%2C%20Xi%2C%20in%20brief%20televised%20comments%2C%20could%20be%20seen%20urging%20President%20Emmanuel%20Macron%20to%20join%20him%20in%20showing%20%26quot%3Bindependence%26quot%3B%2C%20%26quot%3Bprevent%20a%20new%20Cold%20War%26quot%3B%20between%20blocs%2C%20%26quot%3Bwork%20together%20for%20an%20equal%20and%20orderly%20multi-polar%20world%26quot%3B%2C%20and%20oppose%20the%20%26quot%3Bdecoupling%26quot%3B%20of%20China's%20supply%20chains%20and%20other%20economies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBefriending%20The%20Dragon%20Independently%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EScholz%20and%20Xi's%20visits%20can%20be%20seen%20as%20Europe's%20own%20parallel%20engagement%20with%20China%2C%20independent%20of%20that%20of%20the%20US.%20This%20gives%20China%20an%20opportunity%20to%20undercut%20a%20joint%20US-Europe%20front%20against%20it.%3Cbr%3E%5CnFrance%20is%20less%20dependent%20economically%20on%20China%20than%20Germany%2C%20but%20the%20Chinese%20market%20is%20the%20biggest%20one%20for%20its%20luxury%20goods%2C%20besides%20the%20valuable%20Sino-French%20cooperation%20in%20nuclear%2C%20aviation%20and%20agriculture%20areas.%20Germany%20is%20far%20too%20deeply%20tied%20to%20the%20Chinese%20market%20to%20follow%20a%20more%20aggressive%20approach%20towards%20China%20on%20trade%20and%20investment.%20Given%20that%20and%20the%20weakening%20of%20the%20French-German%20tandem%20within%20the%20EU%2C%20Macron%2C%20with%20his%20ambition%20to%20lead%20Europe%2C%20has%20chosen%20to%20take%20the%20lead%20and%20shape%20the%20course%20and%20discourse%20on%20EU-China%20ties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20Scholz%20staying%20away%20from%20a%20joint%20Franco-German%20meeting%20with%20Xi%20Jinping%20-%20something%20the%20French%20President%20would%20have%20preferred%20-%20the%20message%20is%20that%20France%20and%20Germany%20are%20not%20unified%20in%20their%20approach%20towards%20China.%20Nonetheless%2C%20in%20order%20to%20add%20weight%20to%20his%20talks%20with%20Xi%2C%20Macron%20invited%20Ursula%20von%20der%20Leyan%2C%20the%20president%20of%20the%20EU%20Commission%2C%20to%20join%20him%20instead.%20This%20was%20intended%20to%20convey%20the%20message%20that%20he%20was%20speaking%20to%20Xi%20in%20tight%20coordination%20with%20Brussels.%20Macron%2C%20with%20his%20newly%20defined%20vision%20of%20the%20EU%20that%20he%20feels%20will%20alone%20ensure%20Europe's%20survival%2C%20raised%20with%20Xi%20the%20issues%20of%20Europe's%20deficit%20with%20China%2C%20unequal%20market%20access%2C%20China's%20overcapacities%20in%20manufacturing%20and%20the%20consequential%20dumping%20of%20its%20products%20in%20Europe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUrsula%20von%20der%20Leyan%20was%20blunter.%20She%20raised%20the%20issue%20of%20Chinese%20subsidised%20products%2C%20such%20as%20electric%20vehicles%20or%20steel%2C%20which%20are%20flooding%20the%20European%20market%2C%20and%20called%20on%20the%20Chinese%20government%20to%20address%20these%20structural%20overcapacities.%20She%20expanded%20these%20concerns%20by%20stating%20that%20the%20EU%20was%20closely%20coordinating%20with%20the%20G7%20countries%20and%20emerging%20economies%2C%20which%20are%20also%20increasingly%20affected%20by%20China's%20market%20distortions.%20She%20demanded%20real%20progress%20on%20market%20access%20and%20threatened%20to%20make%20full%20use%20of%20the%20EU's%20trade%20defence%20instruments%20if%20necessary%2C%20as%20Europe%20could%20not%20accept%20market-distorting%20practices%20that%20could%20lead%20to%20de-industrialisation%20at%20home.%20She%20also%20spoke%20of%20improving%20the%20resilience%20of%20Europe's%20supply%20chains%20by%20de-risking%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20this%20tough%20talk%20did%20not%20impress%20Xi%20can%20be%20gauged%20from%20his%20reported%20claim%20that%20China's%20over-capacity%20%26quot%3Bdoes%20not%20exist%20either%20from%20the%20perspective%20of%20comparative%20advantage%20or%20in%20light%20of%20global%20demand%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EFault%20Lines%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20the%20US%20and%20the%20EU%20have%20openly%20demanded%20that%20China%20cease%20supporting%20Russia%20militarily%20in%20the%20Ukraine%20conflict.%20The%20possibility%20of%20sanctions%20on%20Beijing%20has%20been%20evoked.%20The%20Atlantic%20partners%20see%20no%20contradiction%20between%20their%20continuing%20support%20to%20Ukraine%2C%20including%20the%20supply%20of%20lethal%20weapons%2C%20and%20their%20opposition%20to%20China%20selling%20some%20precursors%20for%20ammunition%20and%20dual-use%20technologies%20to%20Russia%2C%20its%20strategic%20partner.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMacron%20told%20the%20media%20that%20he%20discussed%20with%20Xi%20Russia's%20war%20of%20aggression%20against%20Ukraine%20and%20conveyed%20to%20him%20that%20without%20security%20for%20Kyiv%2C%20there%20can%20be%20no%20security%20for%20Europe%20(the%20flaw%20in%20this%20argument%20is%20the%20view%20that%20the%20extension%20of%20Russian%20power%20to%20Ukraine%20threatens%20Europe%2C%20but%20the%20extension%20of%20US%20and%20European%20power%20through%20NATO%20to%20Ukraine%20will%20not%20threaten%20Russian%20security).%20Macron%20welcomed%20Xi's%20assurance%20regarding%20Chinese%20commitment%20to%20refrain%20from%20selling%20any%20weapons%20or%20aid%20to%20Moscow%2C%20and%20to%20strictly%20control%20the%20export%20of%20dual-use%20goods.%20Macron%20added%20that%20he%20was%20comforted%20by%20the%20length%20and%20quality%20of%20the%20exchange%20on%20this%20subject.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Rather%20Awkward%20Statement%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESurprisingly%2C%20the%20French%20President%20thanked%20Xi%20for%20%26quot%3Bthis%20moment%20of%20coordination%20that%20you%20wished%20for%20before%20President%20Putin's%20visit%20to%20China%2C%20which%20will%20also%20enable%20us%20to%20have%20a%20common%20agenda%20and%20to%20be%20able%20to%20identify%20whether%20or%20not%20there%20is%20a%20desire%20to%20move%20towards%20...%20lasting%20peace%26quot%3B.%20Whether%20Xi%20was%20embarrassed%20by%20these%20public%20remarks%20about%20coordinating%20with%20France%20before%20his%20own%20discussions%20with%20Putin%2C%20especially%20given%20the%20degradation%20of%20France-Russia%20relations%2C%20can%20be%20a%20matter%20of%20speculation.%20Macron%20also%20raised%20the%20issue%20of%20Chinese%20participation%20in%20the%20Switzerland%20peace%20conference%20on%20the%20Ukraine%20crisis%2C%20and%20reportedly%20received%20a%20non-committal%20response.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMacron's%20statement%20was%20seen%20as%20a%20bid%20to%20commit%20China%20formally%20to%20a%20position%20Xi%20had%20taken%20privately%20on%20Ukraine.%20The%20Chinese%20President's%20response%20to%20this%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20was%20a%20standard%20one.%20China%2C%20he%20said%2C%20did%20not%20start%20the%20Ukraine%20crisis%2C%20nor%20is%20it%20a%20party%20to%20or%20a%20participant%20in%20it.%20He%20emphasised%20that%20instead%20of%20being%20an%20onlooker%2C%20China%20has%20been%20playing%20an%20important%20role%20in%20peace%2C%20with%20its%20special%20representative%20on%20Eurasian%20affairs%20engaging%20in%20shuttle%20diplomacy.%20China%2C%20he%20said%2C%20opposes%20attempts%20to%20use%20the%20Ukraine%20crisis%20to%20scapegoat%20or%20smear%20a%20third%20country%20or%20to%20stoke%20a%20new%20Cold%20War.%20China%20supported%20holding%2C%20at%20a%20proper%20time%2C%20an%20international%20peace%20conference%20that%20is%20recognised%20by%20both%20Russia%20and%20Ukraine%20and%20ensures%20the%20equal%20participation%20of%20all%20parties%20and%20fair%20discussions%20on%20all%20peace%20plans.%20It%20batted%20for%20a%20balanced%2C%20effective%20and%20sustainable%20security%20architecture%20in%20Europe.%20This%20is%20not%20a%20position%20that%20is%20helpful%20for%20either%20France%20or%20the%20EU.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Win-Win%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20in%20all%2C%20Xi%20Jinping%20gained%20enough%20from%20his%20European%20visit%20by%20sending%20a%20message%20of%20China's%20willingness%20to%20further%20open%20up%20its%20economy%2C%20encouraging%20Europe%20to%20be%20more%20independent%20of%20the%20US%2C%20knowing%20also%20that%20American%20protectionism%20was%20hurting%20Europe%20economically.%20He%20also%20projected%20himself%20as%20a%20peacemaker%20and%20put%20out%20a%20strong%20joint%20declaration%20with%20France%20on%20the%20Gaza%20situation.%20Additionally%2C%20the%20agreement%20to%20set%20up%20an%20EV%20factory%20in%20Hungary%20stands%20in%20sharp%20contrast%20to%20the%20talk%20within%20the%20EU%20to%20follow%20the%20US%20in%20imposing%20high%20tariffs%20on%20Chinese%20EV%20imports%2C%20something%20that%20German%20car%20giants%20have%20been%20opposing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrance%20and%20the%20EU%20have%20also%20gained%20by%20engaging%20China%20independently%20of%20the%20US%2C%20sending%20a%20strong%20message%20to%20the%20country%20about%20its%20unfair%20trade%20practices%2C%20and%20pressing%20it%20on%20its%20military%20support%20to%20Russia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20irony%20is%20that%20a%20Europe%20divided%20from%20the%20US%20externally%20and%20over%20economic%20ties%20internally%20can%20hardly%20be%20expected%20to%20deal%20credibly%20with%20the%20China%20challenge.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Kanwal%20Sibal%20was%20Foreign%20Secretary%20and%20Ambassador%20to%20Turkey%2C%20Egypt%2C%20France%2C%20and%20Russia%2C%20and%20Deputy%20Chief%20Of%20Mission%20in%20Washington.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1716455400000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2021-07%2F45evc464_euchina-flag_625x300_12_July_21.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Feurope-china-and-us-an-awkward-love-triangle-5727402%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Even%20in%20an%20adversarial%20atmosphere%2C%20China%20has%20shown%20a%20willingness%20to%20engage%20the%20US.%20Meanwhile%2C%20Europe%20wants%20to%20befriend%20the%20dragon%20despite%20US%20pressures.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Feurope-china-and-us-an-awkward-love-triangle-5727402%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22amp